And the community would get seven more avenues through which to advocate for their priorities and ask questions.

180
00:20:39,164 --> 00:20:41,105
In addition to the public forum of the council meeting,

181
00:20:42,404 --> 00:20:49,207
And the executive branch gets the collaboration of 7 other elected in crafting that budget that tries to meet the community's needs and wants.

182
00:20:50,528 --> 00:21:00,252
I would hope that that could be a really generative collaboration and actually be better for everybody you know again I don't think that I think this is I don't think this is a 0 some proposition.

183
00:21:02,613 --> 00:21:11,898
I also do want to, you know, just again, touch on, you know, it's already been said, I want to acknowledge the hard work of the ongoing Charter Review Commission that process.

184
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:18,122
I know that residents are volunteering and working really hard on that process, it's totally necessary.

185
00:21:18,662 --> 00:21:19,302
It's overdue.

186
00:21:20,963 --> 00:21:28,991
You know, and just to shore up the point that these proposed amendments to specific provisions don't supplant that work at all.

187
00:21:29,372 --> 00:21:36,760
They're targeted proposals that I really do think we could make use of in our very next but will not this budget cycle, but the one after it.

188
00:21:37,460 --> 00:21:38,842
And I think that we need them in place.

189
00:21:39,702 --> 00:21:48,729
you know, for fiscal year 25, you know, we need to empower this council to get its own legislative assets.

190
00:21:50,170 --> 00:21:56,655
And of course, in contrast to that, the Charter Review Commission, that's long-term, that's deliberate, that's gonna be comprehensive.

191
00:21:56,715 --> 00:22:04,442
These are just specific proposals to make sure that we can get what we need in this room, you know, whether that's legal counsel, whether that's the information that we need.

192
00:22:06,063 --> 00:22:08,665
you know, on a faster time track.

193
00:22:08,685 --> 00:22:11,167
So I think that these two tracks, they really do rhyme together.

194
00:22:11,187 --> 00:22:12,788
I don't think that they're in opposition to one another.

195
00:22:12,808 --> 00:22:21,074
I don't think that they, you know, again, that they could have some overlap in a productive way, you know, in three or four years, but these are really urgent.

196
00:22:21,134 --> 00:22:23,956
And so I'm glad that we are getting a jump on them.

197
00:22:23,977 --> 00:22:26,879
I look forward to hearing more feedback, you know, in the next couple of meetings.

198
00:22:26,919 --> 00:22:28,380
So thank you for the time.

199
00:22:29,321 --> 00:22:30,862
Thank you, Councilor Sangmin, Councilor Kavriel.

200
00:22:31,857 --> 00:22:32,738
Thank you, President Morrell.

201
00:22:33,218 --> 00:22:39,784
For me, I'm gonna tell the folks watching at home and in the chamber why I'm excited about this process.

202
00:22:40,144 --> 00:22:49,772
A lot of it overlaps with what's already been said, but ultimately I see this as a tool to help us meet constituents' expectations of what we should be doing.

203
00:22:50,793 --> 00:23:00,821
Could people at home, residents in the city expect the city council to be a branch of government that holds the executive office accountable

204
00:23:01,814 --> 00:23:12,625
Especially during budget season, and they expect us to be legislators as well as well and do that legislative work and to have that legal support to do the work that they voted for us for.

205
00:23:15,296 --> 00:23:19,059
people voted for us with that expectation that we would be able to do that work.

206
00:23:19,519 --> 00:23:23,903
But unfortunately, we don't have the tools right now.

207
00:23:24,584 --> 00:23:34,652
And I think every week, all of us around on this side of the rail, talk about how we're lacking those tools, we talk about

208
00:23:36,273 --> 00:23:38,797
the need for more budget transparency.

209
00:23:38,837 --> 00:23:41,621
We talk about the need for legal representation.

210
00:23:42,602 --> 00:23:45,807
This gives us a chance to act on all that talk.

211
00:23:46,678 --> 00:24:03,292
Um, I think, Councilor Scarpelli speech really underscores and highlights the fact that most of these ideas are ideas that we all share their ideas that aren't us versus them left right center their ideas that are just good for the city that are.

212
00:24:03,972 --> 00:24:06,915
It's good for democracy, good for accountability good for transparency.

213
00:24:07,834 --> 00:24:09,355
I also see this, this.

214
00:24:09,816 --> 00:24:18,262
Another reason why this excites me is, I see it as a compliment to the Charter Review Commission which I think is doing great work, I'm personally very excited for.

215
00:24:20,605 --> 00:24:24,309
This, this is an issue that we didn't all vote for but I did vote yes on it.

216
00:24:24,930 --> 00:24:30,916
Um, and I'm excited to see this be an immediate and urgent compliment to the work that's been doing there.

217
00:24:31,817 --> 00:24:38,464
I'm excited to see us put this in place, hopefully if the voters allow us to.

218
00:24:39,604 --> 00:24:43,667
and excited to see the Charter Review Commission review it as it's in action.

219
00:24:44,447 --> 00:24:59,615
And this gives us a few years to test these proposed amendments, which are active in different cities and the Charter Review Commission in collaboration with residents can decide whether these amendments are working.

220
00:24:59,775 --> 00:25:03,157
But we know something for sure, which is that what we have right now is not working.

221
00:25:04,197 --> 00:25:09,834
Ultimately, I see this as a question of democracy, a question of transparency and the question of accessibility.

222
00:25:11,463 --> 00:25:14,704
I'll talk about, I'll speak to that in two ways, process and substance.

223
00:25:15,524 --> 00:25:26,348
On the process front, this would institute an open process where we, Councilor Behrs mentioned, we'll have more meetings on this.

224
00:25:26,788 --> 00:25:35,271
We get to engage stakeholders across the aisle, across the city, residents can come and speak about these specific proposed amendments.

225
00:25:35,931 --> 00:25:38,752
And ultimately we let them speak in a vote.

226
00:25:39,473 --> 00:25:42,132
I think that's the ultimate democracy.

227
00:25:43,033 --> 00:26:00,322
When it comes to the substance will gain budget transparency, more opportunities and forums for residents to come up to, to, to the podium, or on zoom to speak on the budget, and to speak on issues that affect our whole city and that finance, the financial health of our city.

228
00:26:00,782 --> 00:26:10,126
And ultimately I see it substantively as a, as the institution of a collaboration with the executive office across the aisle across the hall.

229
00:26:12,729 --> 00:26:15,870
that those are just some of the reasons why I'm so excited for this.

230
00:26:17,390 --> 00:26:21,152
With all of my colleagues, I think that we can do really good work here.

231
00:26:23,172 --> 00:26:23,492
Thank you.

232
00:26:23,672 --> 00:26:24,333
Councilor Carvillo.

233
00:26:25,653 --> 00:26:26,653
Thank you, Madam President.

234
00:26:27,153 --> 00:26:30,094
I've sat in this room, I'm going on 12 years now.

235
00:26:31,035 --> 00:26:38,417
And as I go around the community, I hear people, people say that the council's a joke.

236
00:26:39,803 --> 00:26:45,164
I'm tired of people saying that to me, councilors doing anything with nothing.

237
00:26:46,985 --> 00:26:47,805
What's our purpose here?

238
00:26:48,465 --> 00:26:50,885
And this gives us a purpose.

239
00:26:52,826 --> 00:26:58,667
This gives us the tools and the things we need to do to keep us here.

240
00:26:59,747 --> 00:27:03,708
This administration has done its heart to make this council irrelevant.

241
00:27:05,088 --> 00:27:08,669
And this council should be a partner with

242
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,141
the mayor and the rest of the city.

243
00:27:11,781 --> 00:27:21,165
And the way things go right now, we sit here and like I said, like everyone says, things are just thrown at us with no time or no anything.

244
00:27:21,625 --> 00:27:24,566
And let's say there's questions that have to be answered throughout the year.

245
00:27:24,986 --> 00:27:31,769
And let's say, this will give us tools to implement things and keep this council

246
00:27:33,750 --> 00:27:35,051
up to date with what's going on.

247
00:27:35,071 --> 00:27:39,154
I mean, the same people vote for us, vote for the mayor, vote for the school committee.

248
00:27:39,174 --> 00:27:42,297
So we're entitled to the same respect that everyone else gets here.

249
00:27:42,857 --> 00:27:50,964
And this is, in all honesty, this is probably the most unified council that I've sat on in my 12 years.

250
00:27:51,644 --> 00:27:54,947
Because like Council Member Scott says, we're not,

251
00:27:56,294 --> 00:28:01,980
We may not agree on everything but on the major issues in the city, this council is together.

252
00:28:05,124 --> 00:28:06,385
Everyone stands together on this.

253
00:28:07,747 --> 00:28:13,012
In the past, I didn't support the charter review because I had some reservations about it.

254
00:28:14,274 --> 00:28:16,096
I think going forward, that may change.

255
00:28:18,402 --> 00:28:28,187
This package has the tools in it that we need to keep this council relevant and to keep the people informed on what's going on in the community.

256
00:28:30,629 --> 00:28:31,489
Thank you, Councilor Carvalho.

257
00:28:31,749 --> 00:28:33,110
I actually just have two questions.

258
00:28:33,810 --> 00:28:36,352
Also, I want to thank my fellow councilors for their comments.

259
00:28:36,552 --> 00:28:43,716
I agree with pretty much everything that's been said, and I also just want to put a point down again, as everyone has said, thanking the Charter Study Committee.

260
00:28:44,693 --> 00:28:47,014
Like Councilor Collins said, these are things I can run parallel.

261
00:28:47,054 --> 00:28:52,615
I don't want it to seem like this is overrunning the work that you're doing, which is very, very important.

262
00:28:52,635 --> 00:28:57,237
I'm gonna wander into the weeds for two questions.

263
00:28:58,477 --> 00:29:07,680
One is for the commission appointments, can that apply to ad hoc commissions or is it just commissions that are written into the charter?

264
00:29:08,579 --> 00:29:11,961
As this language is written, it would be amendments that are created by ordinance.

265
00:29:12,662 --> 00:29:16,685
So it would not, if the mayor were to appoint ad hoc task forces, that would not apply.

266
00:29:16,705 --> 00:29:21,388
Right, so for example, the Charter Study Committee, that would be something that wouldn't apply.

267
00:29:21,528 --> 00:29:25,531
Of course, the mayor could always submit them for our confirmation if she wanted to, as she could now.

268
00:29:25,951 --> 00:29:34,677
Right, and then this may just be on me to follow up, is just, can public hearings be held in committee or do they have to be held, this is like capital P, capital H public hearings?

269
00:29:34,897 --> 00:29:37,359
I will double check on that, but I believe so.

270
00:29:38,457 --> 00:29:39,158
Great, thank you.

271
00:29:39,958 --> 00:29:40,959
Going back to you, Vice President Harris.

272
00:29:41,359 --> 00:29:42,360
Thank you, Madam President.

273
00:29:43,121 --> 00:29:45,643
And I just wanted to thank my counselors for all of your comments.

274
00:29:45,683 --> 00:30:02,397
I think, you know, if this moves forward and if the voters, you know, if the mayor and the council, if the council votes for it and the mayor agrees to put it on the ballot in a binding way and the voters approve it, it will give us a chance to work together more closely, work together in partnership and have more disagreements.

275
00:30:03,728 --> 00:30:23,553
And that's the work of government right and we work best when we actually are working together and working through disagreements and not not avoiding them or not working together to find the answers, but I just wanted to say a few things about the specific language before before we hear from maybe members of the public, which is one that these are targeted and reasonable amendments.

276
00:30:25,854 --> 00:30:27,234
The budget one specifically.

277
00:30:27,870 --> 00:30:49,728
would say that the mayor would submit the budget by the second Wednesday in May, the council would act by the second Wednesday in June, that the council could not cut the mayor's budget, which we saw almost happened last year, but also at the mayor could not count the council's budget that the council could amend the budget but it couldn't increase it more than the total amount that the mayor has allocated.

278
00:30:51,619 --> 00:30:56,641
It gives a voice, it builds collaboration, it builds relevancy and purpose, but it does so in a targeted way.

279
00:30:56,681 --> 00:31:03,843
This isn't just the council could spend a million dollars more than they want to, or the council could move all the money from the mayor's office to the council budget.

280
00:31:03,883 --> 00:31:05,224
It doesn't allow stuff like that.

281
00:31:05,664 --> 00:31:08,245
It actually asks us to come to the table and work together.

282
00:31:09,385 --> 00:31:18,668
Second is that pretty much all of this language in all of these amendments either exists in another city's charter or is recommended by other cities charter review commissions.

283
00:31:19,129 --> 00:31:21,249
So in that sense, it has been vetted.

284
00:31:22,490 --> 00:31:26,471
The third thing, and I just wanna, I wanna double down here is that this can happen now.

285
00:31:26,551 --> 00:31:34,134
And I think councilor Seng's point that we can do something now to address real problems that we experience almost every meeting.

286
00:31:35,072 --> 00:31:37,254
is important and it's a test bed.

287
00:31:37,634 --> 00:31:40,036
We can put these into the charter, we can see how they work.

288
00:31:40,316 --> 00:31:43,719
If we have, I'm sure that we will find things that we would like to tweak to it.

289
00:31:44,180 --> 00:31:53,147
That can then be part of a comprehensive charter review process that takes, that by law generally will take much more time than this kind of specific targeted process.

290
00:31:53,648 --> 00:32:00,133
And the last thing I wanna say is I actually wanna bring it around to basically what everyone said here in a few different subtexts.

291
00:32:00,954 --> 00:32:02,255
This is about unity.

292
00:32:03,365 --> 00:32:08,069
We may have all of the counselors agreeing that these are tools that the council should have.

293
00:32:08,609 --> 00:32:15,134
I think we have a mayor who sat on this council so much time for 20 years, and also thought that these were tools that the council should have.

294
00:32:15,754 --> 00:32:25,902
And I think that if seven counselors and the mayor are willing to trust the voters and say, these are tools that we think will help government work better and voters, listen to that and say that

295
00:32:26,552 --> 00:32:35,316
they agree to, and they vote to put this in the charter, then we have a council, a mayor, and the public all saying this is a path to move forward.

296
00:32:35,656 --> 00:32:36,717
So that's my hope here.

297
00:32:37,217 --> 00:32:51,404
I know that there's always going to be questions and frustrations and adjustments, and we'll never get 100% of everybody to agree with everything, but I think this is something that can unify people across political differences, ideological differences.

298
00:32:52,924 --> 00:32:57,487
generations, you know, and different beliefs and a really important way to move the city forward.

299
00:32:57,527 --> 00:33:00,749
So that's why I wanted to move us down in this direction.

300
00:33:00,789 --> 00:33:05,212
And I really thank the council for entertaining it and for your thoughtful comments.

301
00:33:05,653 --> 00:33:05,973
Thank you.

302
00:33:06,693 --> 00:33:07,454
Thank you, Vice Mayor Barras.

303
00:33:07,514 --> 00:33:09,615
Any further discussion from the council at this time?

304
00:33:09,635 --> 00:33:15,499
Are there any members of the public who wish to speak either in person or on Zoom?

305
00:33:21,098 --> 00:33:22,459
If you're on Zoom, you can raise your hand.

306
00:33:24,060 --> 00:33:25,061
In person, you can come up.

307
00:33:29,684 --> 00:33:31,325
Not seeing any at this time.

308
00:33:35,188 --> 00:33:40,072
If I could, before that, in the spirit of that motion, two specific motions.

309
00:33:40,192 --> 00:33:46,676
One would be to report this out favorably and place the proposed amendment language on the council agenda for April 25th.

310
00:33:49,077 --> 00:33:51,699
And I'll wait for the clerk to grab that when I have a second motion.

311
00:33:51,719 --> 00:33:54,560
More, did you want to speak or?

312
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:55,581
Okay.

313
00:33:55,601 --> 00:33:57,102
Yeah, you can come right up.

314
00:33:57,122 --> 00:33:58,583
I just saw him shifting, so.

315
00:34:04,106 --> 00:34:06,027
Maury Carroll, 31 Richard Street, Medford.

316
00:34:06,247 --> 00:34:09,729
In all transparency, I am a member of the Charter Review Committee.

317
00:34:10,029 --> 00:34:14,051
I'm speaking more as a citizen and not as a member of that committee.

318
00:34:14,992 --> 00:34:17,914
First of all, I want to applaud the council for once

319
00:34:18,962 --> 00:34:23,384
looking at charter review because every time it's come up previous to this, it's been shot down.

320
00:34:25,205 --> 00:34:27,206
It's almost like we're trying to spot zone here.

321
00:34:27,686 --> 00:34:32,849
And that's a little, George, you mentioned that you got uncomfortable with things on charter review.

322
00:34:33,529 --> 00:34:44,274
Makes me a little uncomfortable too, as a citizen saying, why all of a sudden now, and why are we only looking at specific details when we've talked for years about a total charter review?

323
00:34:44,854 --> 00:34:48,436
And it always falls upon deaf ears and the counselors are the strongest,

324
00:34:49,479 --> 00:34:51,245
opponents to charter review.

325
00:34:52,450 --> 00:34:53,931
which has gone on for years also.

326
00:34:54,231 --> 00:34:57,233
So I applaud you for taking a step forward.

327
00:34:57,253 --> 00:35:10,721
I hope this is just the beginning of how this body and future councils will look at charter review to get this archaic process that we have to live under for the last 40 years that has been changed.

328
00:35:10,761 --> 00:35:12,762
Been a strong mayor for 40 years, everyone knows that.

329
00:35:13,343 --> 00:35:17,845
This council has been put under very difficult restraints because of the charter.

330
00:35:18,426 --> 00:35:21,728
So let's try to keep it all moving forward and work together.

331
00:35:23,078 --> 00:35:23,398
Thank you.

332
00:35:23,838 --> 00:35:24,198
Thank you.

333
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:36,183
Yes, please.

334
00:35:37,263 --> 00:35:37,503
Yes.

335
00:35:40,224 --> 00:35:46,146
And I'll get you that specific language, and I'm actually going to hold off on the second motion week I can make it actually at the meeting on the 20th.

336
00:35:46,166 --> 00:35:47,567
Okay, I have a second on that.

337
00:35:48,679 --> 00:35:50,340
I'll take Councilor Carviello.

338
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,982
So on the motion of Vice President Bexar, seconded by Councilor Carviello.

339
00:35:55,122 --> 00:35:55,862
All those in favor?

340
00:35:55,882 --> 00:35:57,403
All those opposed?

341
00:35:57,603 --> 00:35:58,283
Motion passes.

342
00:35:58,303 --> 00:36:03,165
I'm just gonna do one last call if anyone else would like to speak just because there's a handful of folks on Zoom.

343
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:19,426
Seeing no one else who'd like to speak, do I have on the motion of Councilor Seng to adjourn, seconded by Councilor Collins.

344
00:36:19,446 --> 00:36:20,107
All those in favor?

345
00:36:20,687 --> 00:36:21,408
All those opposed?

346
00:36:21,488 --> 00:36:22,189
Motion passes.

347
00:36:22,269 --> 00:36:22,909
Meeting is adjourned.

